---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const prefaceDescription =
  'Preface to Three Worlds by Dai Pan — how the collection took shape across Still Life, Bless You, and Their World.';
---

<BaseLayout title="Preface" description={prefaceDescription}>
  <main class="preface-page">
    <header class="preface-header">
      <h1>Preface</h1>
      <p class="preface-meta">Dai Pan — 2024–2025</p>
    </header>

    <section class="preface-body">
      <p>
        These poems were written between 2024 and spring 2025, during a stretch of life that felt
        both crowded and empty — cities changing shape, relationships thinning and thickening, the
        self trying to keep up with its own revisions.
      </p>
      <p>
        I did not set out to build a collection. I wrote when language arrived, and I followed it.
        Over time, three tones emerged: a voice that speaks toward power and spectacle (<em>Their
        World</em>), a voice that prays and curses in the same breath (<em>Bless You</em>), and a
        voice that tries to stay close to the ordinary surface of things (<em>Still Life</em>).
      </p>
      <p>
        On this site, each poem is given a layout that responds to its own structure — line count,
        rhythm, density, repetition — and to the time of day in a city tied to each world. The
        reading experience is stable in meaning but unstable in form: the same poem can wear
        different clothes depending on when and where you meet it.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you are reading this before entering the poems, know that nothing here asks for a single
        correct interpretation. These are attempts at honesty, not explanations. Take what holds,
        leave what does not, and move between worlds as you need.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .preface-page {
    padding-left: 0;
    padding-right: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
    max-width: none;
    width: 100%;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .preface-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .preface-header h1 {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
    font-size: var(--type-display);
    line-height: var(--leading-display);
    font-weight: normal;
  }

  .preface-meta {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--type-body);
    color: #1a1a1a;
  }

  .preface-body p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
    font-size: var(--type-body);
    line-height: var(--leading-body);
    color: #1a1a1a;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .preface-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
</style>
